A former coffee roasting mill, commissioned by Wm. Rohnert in 1912, 217 Broadway is a beautifully preserved relic of the great American industrial age. The tangible evidence of its productive past has been carefully curated and remains on premises adding ages of character to the gracious light filled loft space. This is truly a space like no other in Milwaukee. Inside this historic building (included in the National Register of Historic Buildings), the remnants of a building wide network of machinery are exposed to add extraordinary depth of character to contemporary uses. These cast iron machines were made specifically for coffee roasting by Josiah Burns & Sons Machine Foundry in central New York City in 1885. Interconnected between the upper two floors are three coffee roasters, coffee bean storage hoppers, cup electors, and drop chutes mechanically linking the operations between floors and setting an indelible impression for all who enter. Located in the heart of the Historic Third Ward, Milwaukee’s leading creative hub, the neighborhood is home to galleries, offices in 19th century warehouses, performing arts venues like the Broadway Theater Center, and the campus of the Milwaukee Institute of Art & Design. Restaurants are upscale yet approachable; sidewalk dining is popular.

Convert to Residential: An investor can rezone a single parcel or the entire 23-acre site to residential or senior living like the Avalon Hunt Valley and Bright View Senior Living developments across the street at the Hunt Valley Towne Centre. Further, the Portfolio is situated on three land parcels providing the owner the opportunity to phase-in rezoning and development. Sell Individual Buildings to Users: 6 North Park is 26% leased with the top two floors vacant (43,137 SF). Other opportunities to accommodate a user sale include consolidating leases to a single building and when the Travelers’ lease expires. In short, the North Park Office Portfolio provides an investor with immediate scale in one of the strongest submarkets north of Baltimore. Investors may bid on all three buildings or individual buildings. 10 N Park Dr in Hunt Valley MD is convenient to I-695, downtown Baltimore and BWI Airport; surrounded by many fine restaurants, shops, hotels, Oregon Ridge Park, Hunt Valley Towne Centre, and desirable residential communities.

UNDER CONTRACT.  4509-4511 Rhode Island Ave in Brentwood, MD is a single-story flex/industrial warehouse that can accommodate both retail and warehouse uses.  The building includes 7 dock doors, 3 drive-in doors, 22’ ceilings (20’ clear), column spacing of 30’ x 40’, 65 lined parking spaces, plus, approximately 15,000 SF of graded lot area for Industrial Outdoor Storage.  A portion of the building also includes approximately 5,000 SF of mezzanine space (this is not included as part of the building’s RBA of 42,010 SF). The property enjoys two dedicated curb cuts and is well positioned along Rhode Island Ave where the traffic count is over 21,350 vehicles per day.  The property also has access to public transportation with a Metrobus stop immediately in front of the building providing direct access to the Metrorail at the Rhode Island Ave-Brentwood station and the MARC Train to the north at the Riverdale station. When combined with the immediately adjacent 4505 Rhode Island Ave property, the two properties that are owned by the same entity, create a corner lot totaling 2.69 acres making them well positioned for a multi-family development.

The site provides roadside frontage to the south on Crain Hwy allowing for convenient access throughout the region via multiple roadway arteries, including Route-4, Route-301, I-495, and Route-50 all within minutes of the site.

Transwestern’s Mid-Atlantic Multifamily Group, as exclusive agent, is pleased to offer an opportunity to acquire Plaza Towers (the “Property”), a 288-unit high-rise “value-add” opportunity ideally situated in the College Park/Hyattsville submarket in the Washington, DC metro area. The Property is walking distance to Prince George’s Plaza Green Line Metro station, the Target anchored Mall at Prince George’s supporting 1,500 employees, and University Town Center with office and retail supporting 3,500 employees. Less than one mile to University of Maryland at College Park, the exceptional location provides access to some of the region’s largest employment drivers throughout the region and in downtown Washington, DC. Plaza Towers has been institutionally owned by both previous and current ownership with significant high-cost capital improvements completed positioning the Property for continuation of a successful interior unit renovation program with actual in-place premiums ranging from $100 for a Studio to $300 for a Three-bedroom, supported by common area upgrades including updated lobby, building entry, common area hallways, leasing office and community amenities.
